title: China Donates 50,000 NAD to Windhoek City, Namibia (Linked to #62615)
description: On 7 December 2018 at a Christmas event, the Chinese Embassy in Namibia granted 50,000 NAD to the city of Windhoek for unspecified purposes. This donation could be for the "free" medical clinic offered at the Christmas party. The 12th Chinese medical team (project #62628) carried out the consultations for roughly 400 elderly Namibians in attendance.   The following day, the Chinese Embassy donated another N$100,000 to elderly Namibians at different Christmas party (project #62615).
combined_text:
# Sector
UNALLOCATED/UNSPECIFIED

# Title
China Donates 50,000 NAD to Windhoek City, Namibia (Linked to #62615)

# Description
On 7 December 2018 at a Christmas event, the Chinese Embassy in Namibia granted 50,000 NAD to the city of Windhoek for unspecified purposes. This donation could be for the "free" medical clinic offered at the Christmas party. The 12th Chinese medical team (project #62628) carried out the consultations for roughly 400 elderly Namibians in attendance.   The following day, the Chinese Embassy donated another N$100,000 to elderly Namibians at different Christmas party (project #62615).
justification: Donation for unspecified purposes, likely supporting social welfare activities
evidence: Donation to city of Windhoek, connection to medical clinic and elderly support

title: China Donates 100,000 NAD worth of Hygienic Supplies to Namibia (Linked to #67797)
description: On November 16, 2018, the Chinese Embassy to Namibia donated 100,000 NAD worth of hygienic supplies to combat spreading the ongoing hepatitis-E outbreak. The official donation ceremony took place at a clinic event co-organized by the Embassy, the Chinese-funded Chamber of Commerce, and the Red Cross Society in which the 12th medical team provided free consultations (#67797).
combined_text:
# Sector
HEALTH

# Title
China Donates 100,000 NAD worth of Hygienic Supplies to Namibia (Linked to #67797)

# Description
On November 16, 2018, the Chinese Embassy to Namibia donated 100,000 NAD worth of hygienic supplies to combat spreading the ongoing hepatitis-E outbreak. The official donation ceremony took place at a clinic event co-organized by the Embassy, the Chinese-funded Chamber of Commerce, and the Red Cross Society in which the 12th medical team provided free consultations (#67797).
justification: Project focuses on healthcare support and disease prevention without direct environmental or energy transition impacts
evidence: Donation of hygienic supplies, medical consultations, health sector focus

title: China Pledges 200,000 NAD to St. Boniface College in Namibia for Textbooks
description: On September 14, 2018, the Chinese Embassy pledged to donate 200,000 NAD to St. Boniface College, a private secondary school, in Kavango East Province to spend on textbooks. It is unclear whether these funds have actually been disbursed. At the same ceremony, a number of Chinese Ambassador Scholarships were awarded (#67765).

title: China Donates 50,000 NAD to Mini World Cup among Namibian Elementary Schools
description: On June 26, 2018, the Chinese Ambassador to Namibia donated 50,000 NAD to the Mini World Cup, a fundraiser jointly organized by more than 40 elementary schools in Khomas Province to celebrate the World Cup in Russia and raise money for a sports field and mixed-use courts for netball, volleyball, and basketball. The launch ceremony took place at Mao Zedong Middle School (#41119).

title: China sends 12th Medical Team to Namibia (Linked to #67797, Umbrella Project #62439)
description: On 8 June 2018, the 12th Chinese medical team was officially welcomed in Namibia. The team consisting of four doctors and nurses with backgrounds in traditional Chinese medicine served in Katutura Hospital in Windhoek until 20 January 2020.    The 12th medical team has carried out multiple free consultations (project #67797), especially related to the ongoing hepatitis-E outbreak.  This project is part of the umbrella project #62439, which captures all medical teams sent to Katutura State Hospital since 1996.
staff_comments: This project could be related to donation captured in ProjectID#62616.
combined_text:
# Sector
HEALTH

# Title
China sends 12th Medical Team to Namibia (Linked to #67797, Umbrella Project #62439)

# Description
On 8 June 2018, the 12th Chinese medical team was officially welcomed in Namibia. The team consisting of four doctors and nurses with backgrounds in traditional Chinese medicine served in Katutura Hospital in Windhoek until 20 January 2020.    The 12th medical team has carried out multiple free consultations (project #67797), especially related to the ongoing hepatitis-E outbreak.  This project is part of the umbrella project #62439, which captures all medical teams sent to Katutura State Hospital since 1996.
justification: Project is focused on healthcare services without direct environmental or energy transition impacts
evidence: Medical team deployment, healthcare services, traditional Chinese medicine focus

title: China Funds and Builds Greenhouses in Namibia (Linked to Project ID#88520).
description: On June 28, 2018, the Chinese Ambassador visited Embassy-donated greenhouses but constructed and operated by the Youth League of the People's Organizing Party Kavango East branch. The Chinese Embassy donated at least 4 greenhouses, with 8 possible being committed as cited by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs for the PRC. The produce will support the community's consumption needs.
staff_comments: See project #88520 for the 2019 greenhouse donation.
combined_text:
# Sector
AGRICULTURE, FORESTRY, FISHING

# Title
China Funds and Builds Greenhouses in Namibia (Linked to Project ID#88520).

# Description
On June 28, 2018, the Chinese Ambassador visited Embassy-donated greenhouses but constructed and operated by the Youth League of the People's Organizing Party Kavango East branch. The Chinese Embassy donated at least 4 greenhouses, with 8 possible being committed as cited by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs for the PRC. The produce will support the community's consumption needs.
justification: Project focuses on agricultural development and community support without clear environmental or energy transition impacts
evidence: Greenhouse construction for community consumption needs, social development focus
